#
# Run the bitcoin client, connecting to the regtest network
#
# The other network are:
#
# main		The main (production network). This is the default network.
# testnet	The test network.
#
# Use --help get a list of the client options
#
# If a server is running, use the RPC 
#
#    run.bitcoin-cli help 
#
# to get a list of server RPCs
#
# Use the parameters -rpcconnect=<ip> -rpcuser=<user> -rpcpassword=<pw>
#
# to connect to a remote server.
#
./bitcoin-cli -regtest "$@"
